==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From Middle English '''bene''' < Old English [[bēan]] (bean, pea, legume) < Proto-Germanic '''*baunō''', of unknown origin.

===Pronunciation===
*bēn, /biːn/, /<tt>bi:n</tt>/
*:'''Homophones''': [[been]]
*:[[Rhymes:English:-iːn|Rhymes: -iːn]]

===Noun===
'''bean''' (''plural:'' [[beans]])

#The large edible seed of plants of several genera of ''Fabaceae''.
#The seed [[pod]] of plants of several genera of ''Fabaceae''.

====Translations====
'''large edible seed of ''Fabaceae'''''
